1. In vim, type â€œmkdirâ€, click â€˜one spaceâ€™, type â€œ.â€ and then type file name in order to create a hidden file. For example â€œmkdir .fileâ€
	To display it, type â€œls -aâ€, if you type only â€œlsâ€, you cannot see the hidden file you have just created. But if you type â€œls -aâ€, you can see 3 hidden files and one of them is the file you have just created.

